You caused an incident?

516
00:33:24.340 --> 00:33:25.383
Seriously? [clicks tongue]

517
00:33:25.466 --> 00:33:27.635
-There was a fire.
-A fire?

518
00:33:27.719 --> 00:33:29.721
Wait. A fire?

519
00:33:29.804 --> 00:33:32.306
What about the Grand Prince? Is he okay?

520
00:33:33.891 --> 00:33:35.184
Ms. Do.

521
00:33:35.268 --> 00:33:36.728
Are you a fan of Prince I-AN?

522
00:33:37.937 --> 00:33:39.230
Me?

523
00:33:40.189 --> 00:33:41.190
[scoffs]

524
00:33:43.443 --> 00:33:44.485
I meanâ€¦

525
00:33:48.573 --> 00:33:51.284
[reporter] <i>An explosion has occurred</i>
<i>at Junghwajeon Hall.</i>

526
00:33:51.367 --> 00:33:54.162
<i>It occurred during</i>
<i>the Royal Birthday Banquet.</i>

527
00:33:54.245 --> 00:33:58.416
<i>but fortunately.</i>
<i>no casualties have been reported.</i>

528
00:33:58.499 --> 00:34:00.376
<i>The police and fire departmentâ€¦</i>

529
00:34:03.337 --> 00:34:04.881
[Ms. Do] Is there some bad blood?

530
00:34:05.590 --> 00:34:06.591
What?

531
00:34:06.674 --> 00:34:10.178
Grand Prince I-AN also attended
the Royal Academy of Korea.

532
00:34:10.261 --> 00:34:13.056
I thought you might've been
bullied or something.

533
00:34:13.139 --> 00:34:14.390
You're so hostile toward him.

534
00:34:14.474 --> 00:34:15.892
[scoffs]

535
00:34:15.975 --> 00:34:17.101
Yeah. right.

536
00:34:18.394 --> 00:34:21.147
Do I look like someone
who would be bullied?

537
00:34:21.230 --> 00:34:22.273
[chuckles]

538
00:34:22.356 --> 00:34:23.357
That's true.

539
00:34:24.275 --> 00:34:25.735
Then why do you hate him so much?

540
00:34:27.195 --> 00:34:28.196
Just because.

541
00:34:30.406 --> 00:34:31.491
He's obnoxious.

542
00:34:33.326 --> 00:34:35.328
[â™ª gentle music playing]

543
00:34:39.499 --> 00:34:41.667
Please work. Come on.

544
00:34:43.127 --> 00:34:44.170
Please.

545
00:34:45.004 --> 00:34:46.255
[sighs]

546
00:35:06.442 --> 00:35:07.443
[sighs]

547
00:35:15.535 --> 00:35:16.744
[sighs]

548
00:35:19.247 --> 00:35:20.248
[sighs]

549
00:35:26.462 --> 00:35:27.463
[I-AN] Who goes there?

550
00:35:29.966 --> 00:35:31.384
[â™ª gentle music playing]

551
00:35:44.814 --> 00:35:48.359
If you've done wrong.
you must accept a fair punishment.

552
00:35:49.026 --> 00:35:51.404
Don't disgrace yourself
by getting caught in flight.

553
00:35:51.487 --> 00:35:52.822
Name.

554
00:35:58.619 --> 00:35:59.745
It's Seong Huiju.

555
00:36:00.329 --> 00:36:01.539
Affiliation.

556
00:36:03.833 --> 00:36:06.544
Jujak House. Ninth grade.

557
00:36:06.627 --> 00:36:08.337
You know you violated school regulations.

558
00:36:08.421 --> 00:36:11.716
I needed more training time.
The exhibition match is coming up--

559
00:36:11.799 --> 00:36:13.593
Are you a man of virtue or of profit?

560
00:36:15.845 --> 00:36:16.846
[sighs]

561
00:36:16.929 --> 00:36:19.140
Students under tenth grade are prohibited

562
00:36:19.223 --> 00:36:21.058
from leaving the dormitory after 11 p.m.

563
00:36:21.142 --> 00:36:23.561
Violation of this rule
results in 20 demerit points.

564
00:36:23.644 --> 00:36:25.855
Use of facilities
outside designated training hours

565
00:36:25.938 --> 00:36:27.857
requires prior approval
from the principal.

566
00:36:27.940 --> 00:36:30.401
Violation of this rule
results in 10 demerit points.

567
00:36:30.484 --> 00:36:32.445
-In totalâ€¦
-And Your Royal Highness?

568
00:36:33.404 --> 00:36:35.072
You are here too. are you not?

569
00:36:35.907 --> 00:36:37.867
Will you receive demerit points as well?

570
00:36:45.750 --> 00:36:47.293
I'm here with approval.

571
00:36:51.505 --> 00:36:53.174
ARCHERY RANGE USAGE APPROVAL

572
00:36:54.592 --> 00:36:55.718
How'd you get this?

573
00:36:55.801 --> 00:36:59.472
After all that talk about students getting
carried away for the exhibition match

574
00:36:59.555 --> 00:37:02.725
and the archery range not being
meant for individual training?

575
00:37:08.606 --> 00:37:11.734
I got this key from Ryu Minseok.
Cheongnyong House. ninth grade.

576
00:37:11.817 --> 00:37:13.694
-Ryu Minseok?
-Yes.

577
00:37:13.778 --> 00:37:16.030
He was shamelessly bragging
about having this key.

578
00:37:16.113 --> 00:37:17.198
so I stole it.

579
00:37:17.281 --> 00:37:18.574
[sighs]

580
00:37:18.658 --> 00:37:21.535
I'm not sure why an individual
had a key to this archery range

581
00:37:21.619 --> 00:37:23.955
when it's not a place
for individual training.

582
00:37:25.748 --> 00:37:27.458
[sighs]

583
00:37:27.541 --> 00:37:30.211
But seeing how easily
you obtained this approval notice.

584
00:37:31.212 --> 00:37:33.589
I guess it was only out of reach for me.

585
00:37:36.384 --> 00:37:38.719
So do not lecture me
about demerit points or whatever.

586
00:37:38.803 --> 00:37:39.804
I intend

587
00:37:40.429 --> 00:37:42.431
to enjoy every opportunity

588
00:37:43.224 --> 00:37:44.350
my enemy enjoys.

589
00:37:44.433 --> 00:37:46.018
You wish to stoop to their level?

590
00:37:46.102 --> 00:37:48.229
I'd rather play dirty and win

591
00:37:48.312 --> 00:37:50.606
than play clean and lose.

592
00:37:57.613 --> 00:37:58.656
[scoffs]

593
00:38:14.130 --> 00:38:15.298
[scoffs]

594
00:38:17.091 --> 00:38:18.259
So obnoxious.

595
00:38:22.054 --> 00:38:23.389
[sighs]

596
00:38:40.364 --> 00:38:43.492
[court lady] Your Royal Highness.
The Queen Mother has arrived.

597
00:38:47.288 --> 00:38:48.289
Escort her in.

598
00:38:59.091 --> 00:39:00.801
{\an8}IN TIMES OF PEACE.
DO NOT FORGET DANGER

599
00:39:00.885 --> 00:39:02.762
{\an8}IN TIMES OF PROSPERITY.
DO NOT FORGET RUIN

600
00:39:02.845 --> 00:39:04.597
{\an8}IN TIMES OF ORDER.
DO NOT FORGET CHAOS

601
00:39:16.400 --> 00:39:17.526
Must I wait longer?

602
00:39:21.447 --> 00:39:22.448
Grand Prince.

603
00:39:24.325 --> 00:39:25.493
Yes?

604
00:39:26.869 --> 00:39:27.953
About yesterdayâ€¦

605
00:39:31.123 --> 00:39:32.124
I regret my actions.

606
00:39:34.335 --> 00:39:36.087
I was not in my right mind.

607
00:39:37.380 --> 00:39:39.465
I feared some misfortune
had struck His Majesty.

608
00:39:39.548 --> 00:39:41.592
Prime Minister Min
has asked for the details

609
00:39:42.635 --> 00:39:44.387
of how the Queen Mother

610
00:39:44.470 --> 00:39:47.807
dared to strike the Grand Prince
and lash out with such unspeakable words.

611
00:39:50.101 --> 00:39:51.185
So I hear.

612
00:39:55.940 --> 00:39:57.149
Do not worry.

613
00:39:58.734 --> 00:40:00.694
I shall tell him you took responsibility

614
00:40:01.529 --> 00:40:02.655
and expressed remorse

615
00:40:04.198 --> 00:40:05.533
for your actions.

616
00:40:09.078 --> 00:40:11.497
No one shows concern for His Majesty.

617
00:40:12.706 --> 00:40:13.999
The palace was on fire.

618
00:40:14.959 --> 00:40:16.585
and the King almost died.

619
00:40:18.295 --> 00:40:21.549
Yet all anyone seems to care about
is the scratch on your cheek.

620
00:40:21.632 --> 00:40:22.842
Am I to blame for that?

621
00:40:22.925 --> 00:40:25.428
Yes. you are. You are the regent.

622
00:40:33.936 --> 00:40:36.522
His Majesty is a mere eight years of age.

623
00:40:36.605 --> 00:40:38.899
Far too young
to be overseeing state affairs.

624
00:40:40.067 --> 00:40:41.485
So my regency is unavoidable.

625
00:40:44.530 --> 00:40:45.781
-I-ANâ€¦
-Furthermore.

626
00:40:47.366 --> 00:40:49.243
a regent holds no special powers.

627
00:40:49.326 --> 00:40:50.661
-I-AN!
-Politiciansâ€¦

628
00:40:53.539 --> 00:40:55.207
engage in politics.

629
00:40:57.334 --> 00:40:58.961
Peddlers engage in business.

630
00:41:05.801 --> 00:41:07.470
The monarchy remains passive.

631
00:41:09.305 --> 00:41:11.140
Simply doing nothingâ€¦

632
00:41:13.851 --> 00:41:15.102
is its sole duty.

633
00:41:18.814 --> 00:41:21.400
Have you ever considered that
to be true power?

634
00:41:22.735 --> 00:41:23.986
The politicians

635
00:41:24.570 --> 00:41:27.573
burn with fervor
to claim a place at your side.

636
00:41:28.782 --> 00:41:30.993
Because a single photo taken beside you

637
00:41:31.494 --> 00:41:34.413
wields greater power than ten pledges
wrought with painstaking care.

638
00:41:35.206 --> 00:41:36.457
And the business elites?

639
00:41:36.540 --> 00:41:40.336
They hasten to attend to you
on every diplomatic tour.

640
00:41:40.419 --> 00:41:43.506
The mere fact that you granted them
a place by your side

641
00:41:45.090 --> 00:41:47.218
is enough to gain
the trust of their investors.

642
00:41:51.222 --> 00:41:52.264
You eclipseâ€¦

643
00:41:56.060 --> 00:41:57.603
the Crown itself.

644
00:42:04.193 --> 00:42:06.195
[â™ª emotional music playing]

645
00:42:09.365 --> 00:42:10.491
Father.

646
00:42:10.574 --> 00:42:13.244
I have received a 100 on my exam.

647
00:42:17.248 --> 00:42:19.458
-Rise above such trifles.
-Sorry?

648
00:42:19.542 --> 00:42:21.669
If it be remarkable.
it is but the natural order.

649
00:42:21.752 --> 00:42:22.962
If it be lacking.

650
00:42:23.546 --> 00:42:25.422
it is but a cause for shame.

651
00:42:25.506 --> 00:42:27.049
But Father.

652
00:42:27.132 --> 00:42:30.427
is diligence not
the duty of a man of virtue?

653
00:42:30.511 --> 00:42:33.889
You are a Grand Prince
before you are a man of virtue.

654
00:42:33.973 --> 00:42:35.307
I-SHIN

655
00:42:35.391 --> 00:42:37.268
That is your new royal title.

656
00:42:38.811 --> 00:42:41.939
My royal title is to change?

657
00:42:42.022 --> 00:42:44.525
It is a reminder to remain true and just.

658
00:42:46.777 --> 00:42:49.154
Do not stand in the way
of the Crown Prince.

659
00:43:02.668 --> 00:43:04.712
This is your new royal title.

660
00:43:05.421 --> 00:43:06.964
I-AN

661
00:43:08.799 --> 00:43:09.883
Am I beingâ€¦

662
00:43:12.886 --> 00:43:13.887
rewarded again?

663
00:43:27.026 --> 00:43:28.027
And soâ€¦

664
00:43:30.571 --> 00:43:31.947
what do you seek from me?

665
00:43:33.240 --> 00:43:35.576
That you be His Majesty's steadfast
pillar of support.

666
00:43:35.659 --> 00:43:37.286
I already serve in that capacity.

667
00:43:38.245 --> 00:43:39.622
Proceed to your nuptials.

668
00:43:43.042 --> 00:43:45.210
Wed the woman of my choosing

669
00:43:46.462 --> 00:43:49.590
and demonstrate your allegiance
to His Majesty and me.

670
00:44:01.143 --> 00:44:02.936
[Huiju] <i>I told you I don't want to.</i>

671
00:44:04.813 --> 00:44:06.357
[sighs] Fine.

672
00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:09.360
Let's say I concede to everything.
and I do get married.

673
00:44:10.027 --> 00:44:14.031
I am still an heir to a conglomerate.
so strategic M&A is certainly important.

674
00:44:14.573 --> 00:44:17.201
That's my role
in fortifying the family's legacy.

675
00:44:17.284 --> 00:44:19.828
But the CEO of a mere subsidiary
simply will not do.

676
00:44:19.912 --> 00:44:21.455
Do you think that makes any sense?

677
00:44:21.538 --> 00:44:22.706
I'm Seong Huiju!

678
00:44:22.790 --> 00:44:24.249
[Taeju] So what if you are?

679
00:44:24.917 --> 00:44:26.001
Father. we're here.

680
00:44:26.669 --> 00:44:27.670
Hey.

681
00:44:27.753 --> 00:44:29.630
Must you be so loud?

682
00:44:29.713 --> 00:44:31.423
All you do is bark day and night.

683
00:44:31.507 --> 00:44:33.717
Hello. Father. Huiju.

684
00:44:33.801 --> 00:44:35.386
Honey. you want a cup?

685
00:44:35.469 --> 00:44:37.596
-So hot!
-You should be more careful. honey.

686
00:44:37.680 --> 00:44:38.972
[exclaims]

687
00:44:39.056 --> 00:44:40.057
You could've warned me.

688
00:44:43.435 --> 00:44:46.313
Don't pester Father too much. Huiju.

689
00:44:46.397 --> 00:44:48.607
He went to great lengths

690
00:44:48.691 --> 00:44:51.193
to find a proper suitor for you.

691
00:44:51.276 --> 00:44:53.195
[Mr. Seong sighs]

692
00:44:53.821 --> 00:44:54.988
[scoffs]

693
00:44:55.489 --> 00:44:57.366
So you two collaborated on this?

694
00:44:57.991 --> 00:44:59.785
And this is the result?

695
00:44:59.868 --> 00:45:02.413
A nobody who doesn't even make
the industry rankings?

696
00:45:02.496 --> 00:45:04.373
Shall I use him as a trophy boyfriend?

697
00:45:04.456 --> 00:45:06.041
Why you littleâ€¦

698
00:45:06.917 --> 00:45:08.168
[clicks tongue]

699
00:45:08.252 --> 00:45:10.045
Our hands are tied.

700
00:45:10.713 --> 00:45:12.381
When it comes to arranged marriages.

701
00:45:12.464 --> 00:45:15.467
most families tend
to nitpick every detail.

702
00:45:15.551 --> 00:45:16.552
"Every detail"?

703
00:45:18.679 --> 00:45:19.888
"Every detail"?

704
00:45:20.556 --> 00:45:22.808
[laughs]

705
00:45:22.891 --> 00:45:26.812
So you also nitpicked "every detail"
and ended up with this loser?

706
00:45:26.895 --> 00:45:28.397
That's strange.

707
00:45:28.480 --> 00:45:31.316
With all that nitpicking.
you had to see the marriage was doomed.

708
00:45:31.400 --> 00:45:34.737
-Hey. we married for love!
-Who cares what the in-laws' pet thinks?

709
00:45:34.820 --> 00:45:36.655
-What was that?
-That's enough!

710
00:45:38.365 --> 00:45:40.701
[sighs] She's just impossible.

711
00:45:41.618 --> 00:45:43.746
As you said.
you'll eventually have to marry.

712
00:45:43.829 --> 00:45:45.372
Who said I didn't want to marry?

713
00:45:45.456 --> 00:45:47.958
I just don't want to marry
someone that far beneath me.

714
00:45:48.041 --> 00:45:49.084
[Taeju scoffs]

715
00:45:49.168 --> 00:45:52.004
[Huiju] Father. just be honest with me.

716
00:45:52.087 --> 00:45:54.256
You want to take this chance
to get rid of me. no?

717
00:45:54.339 --> 00:45:57.259
Because based on pure competence.
that jerk wouldn't stand a chance.

718
00:45:57.342 --> 00:46:00.220
Hey. who wouldn't stand a chance?

719
00:46:00.304 --> 00:46:01.805
You. obviously. Certainly not me!

720
00:46:03.265 --> 00:46:04.391
[sighs]

721
00:46:05.976 --> 00:46:07.644
I guess branding me illegitimate

722
00:46:07.728 --> 00:46:10.439
and saddling me
with a useless brother wasn't enough?

723
00:46:10.522 --> 00:46:13.650
Now you want to foist
an incompetent husband upon me as well?

724
00:46:15.319 --> 00:46:16.779
This will not go

725
00:46:17.738 --> 00:46:19.072
as you wish. Father.

726
00:46:20.657 --> 00:46:22.409
I won't let that happen.

727
00:46:29.291 --> 00:46:30.417
[Hyeon] <i>Nuptials?</i>

728
00:46:30.501 --> 00:46:32.544
[stammers] Did you agree to it?

729
00:46:34.171 --> 00:46:35.631
Maybe.

730
00:46:35.714 --> 00:46:36.715
You're really going to?

731
00:46:39.760 --> 00:46:40.803
Why not?

732
00:46:40.886 --> 00:46:42.679
[Hyeon exclaims]

733
00:46:42.763 --> 00:46:46.308
Since when did Your Royal Highness
become so obedient?

734
00:46:48.060 --> 00:46:49.978
And since when have you grown so insolent?

735
00:46:52.856 --> 00:46:53.857
My apologies. sir.

736
00:46:53.941 --> 00:46:56.443
I'm just frustrated
with the situation. that's all.

737
00:46:56.527 --> 00:46:59.488
I mean. all this time.
she was firmly against your nuptials.

738
00:46:59.571 --> 00:47:01.824
And now. she wants you to get married?

739
00:47:01.907 --> 00:47:04.034
To a woman she chooses. no less?

740
00:47:04.117 --> 00:47:05.577
This is downright unreasonable.

741
00:47:05.661 --> 00:47:07.246
[clicks tongue] Darn it.

742
00:47:08.872 --> 00:47:10.874
[sighs]

743
00:47:15.337 --> 00:47:17.256
We did this last year.

744
00:47:18.590 --> 00:47:20.425
And this is what our competitor is doing.

745
00:47:21.885 --> 00:47:24.888
[sighs] Did you need
more time or something?

746
00:47:25.722 --> 00:47:27.724
Ms. Seong. the thing about PR is--

747
00:47:27.808 --> 00:47:30.352
Don't tell me there are only
so many ways to spin it.

748
00:47:30.853 --> 00:47:33.397
If that's your excuse. you should resign.

749
00:47:33.480 --> 00:47:35.399
You're saying anyone could do your job.

750
00:47:35.482 --> 00:47:38.068
If it's all the same.
why carry a bloated payroll?

751
00:47:38.151 --> 00:47:39.486
My apologies.

752
00:47:40.571 --> 00:47:43.365
We'll revise based on your feedback
and get back to you. ma'am.

753
00:47:44.658 --> 00:47:45.784
[Huiju sighs]

754
00:47:48.287 --> 00:47:49.621
[clicks tongue]

755
00:47:52.541 --> 00:47:54.459
[door closes]

756
00:47:55.127 --> 00:47:56.879
[sighs]

757
00:47:59.756 --> 00:48:00.757
[Ms. Do] Here we go.

758
00:48:04.428 --> 00:48:06.096
Drink some. It's lotus root tea.

759
00:48:11.476 --> 00:48:12.936
Isn't this super bitter?

760
00:48:13.020 --> 00:48:15.731
Come on. Just drink it.

761
00:48:15.814 --> 00:48:17.649
It soothes pent-up anger.

762
00:48:18.233 --> 00:48:19.651
I don't have any pent-up anger.

763
00:48:19.735 --> 00:48:22.112
You've been riding the staff for days now.

764
00:48:25.032 --> 00:48:28.410
Listen. I know you're on edge
with the marriage issue and all.

765
00:48:28.493 --> 00:48:30.579
but don't drag personal issues
into the workplace.

766
00:48:31.163 --> 00:48:32.998
-You look really petty.
-What?

767
00:48:33.081 --> 00:48:34.207
"Petty"?

768
00:48:35.042 --> 00:48:37.169
Who? Me?

769
00:48:37.252 --> 00:48:39.755
Ms. Do. I am Seong Huiju!

770
00:48:40.380 --> 00:48:42.090
Yeah. sure. Here.

771
00:48:44.343 --> 00:48:46.511
-[huffs]
-Go on.

772
00:48:47.554 --> 00:48:48.555
[in English] Drink it.

773
00:48:55.771 --> 00:48:56.939
[in Korean] So bitter.

774
00:49:01.568 --> 00:49:05.364
[â™ª tense music playing]

775
00:49:14.915 --> 00:49:16.041
[chuckles]

776
00:49:17.501 --> 00:49:18.627
Your Royal Highness.

777
00:49:19.711 --> 00:49:20.712
Lord INPYEONG.

778
00:49:21.838 --> 00:49:24.049
It appears you are leaving the palace.

779
00:49:25.217 --> 00:49:27.177
Yes. I am taking some time off.

780
00:49:27.761 --> 00:49:28.762
"Time off"?

781
00:49:28.845 --> 00:49:32.432
His Majesty's birthday preparations
had me held up in the palace for a while.

782
00:49:33.892 --> 00:49:34.977
[sighs]

783
00:49:35.060 --> 00:49:37.688
I intend to spend a few days resting
at my private residence.

784
00:49:37.771 --> 00:49:39.606
Your private residence?

785
00:49:39.690 --> 00:49:42.526
Then who will safeguard the palace.
Your Royal Highness?

786
00:49:42.609 --> 00:49:46.238
What would we do
if you were to leave the palace alone

787
00:49:46.321 --> 00:49:47.614
and misfortune befell you?

788
00:49:50.575 --> 00:49:52.703
I thought you would welcome my absence.

789
00:49:56.915 --> 00:49:58.000
[chuckles]

790
00:49:58.500 --> 00:50:00.794
[laughs]

791
00:50:01.753 --> 00:50:04.256
Perhaps I was under the wrong impression.

792
00:50:05.382 --> 00:50:07.259
Please give my best to Queen Mother.

793
00:50:07.843 --> 00:50:12.055
I was so excited about my time off
that I forgot to pay my respects.

794
00:50:14.391 --> 00:50:15.392
[chuckles]

795
00:50:30.824 --> 00:50:33.285
[Lord INPYEONG]
Is that what you said to him?

796
00:50:35.328 --> 00:50:37.164
It was His Majesty's royal birthday.

797
00:50:38.498 --> 00:50:40.167
He showed up lateâ€¦

798
00:50:41.501 --> 00:50:42.753
wearing a <i>cheollik.</i>

799
00:50:43.253 --> 00:50:45.297
A fire even broke out.

800
00:50:45.380 --> 00:50:46.631
That was all I-AN--

801
00:50:46.715 --> 00:50:47.716
Your Majesty.

802
00:50:56.308 --> 00:50:58.268
And the members of the royal family?

803
00:50:58.894 --> 00:51:02.064
Despite tirelessly preaching propriety.
they do not dare utter

804
00:51:02.147 --> 00:51:04.900
a single word of remonstrance
before the Grand Prince.

805
00:51:07.903 --> 00:51:09.905
The people cherish the Grand Prince.

806
00:51:10.530 --> 00:51:11.907
[scoffs]

807
00:51:11.990 --> 00:51:14.284
Even after losing his parents and brother.

808
00:51:15.077 --> 00:51:17.871
he continues to serve
as regent for his nephew.

809
00:51:17.954 --> 00:51:20.624
safeguarding the Crown.

810
00:51:24.711 --> 00:51:26.463
That is precisely the issue.

811
00:51:29.007 --> 00:51:31.176
His Majesty is but a child.
throwing the disparity

812
00:51:31.760 --> 00:51:35.263
between him and the Grand Prince
behind him into even starker relief.

813
00:51:47.150 --> 00:51:48.902
KIM YEONGHUN.
CEO OF SEONGSAN TEXTILE

814
00:51:48.985 --> 00:51:50.070
[Ms. Do] <i>None of them?</i>

815
00:51:50.570 --> 00:51:51.780
[Huiju] Come on.

816
00:51:52.322 --> 00:51:55.826
How are they any different
from the men Father picked?

817
00:51:55.909 --> 00:51:58.995
At least be handsome if you're
a lost cause in the corporate rankings.

818
00:51:59.079 --> 00:52:00.997
No money.

819
00:52:01.081 --> 00:52:02.749
No looks to speak of.

820
00:52:02.833 --> 00:52:03.917
Tsk. tsk. tsk.

821
00:52:04.876 --> 00:52:07.254
What about politicians?
No candidates there?

822
00:52:07.921 --> 00:52:09.464
Why is it all businessmen?

823
00:52:09.548 --> 00:52:11.925
Politicians don't like mixing
with business people.

824
00:52:12.008 --> 00:52:14.761
[scoffs] They love money
but hate business people?

825
00:52:14.845 --> 00:52:16.304
Too much potential baggage.

826
00:52:16.388 --> 00:52:18.807
-Illegal succession. tax evasionâ€¦
-What?

827
00:52:19.474 --> 00:52:20.559
That's ridiculous.

828
00:52:20.642 --> 00:52:23.103
Either way. politicians are a no-go.

829
00:52:23.186 --> 00:52:25.689
They traditionally prefer aristocrats.

830
00:52:25.772 --> 00:52:27.607
Aristocrats? You must be kidding.

831
00:52:27.691 --> 00:52:30.485
Are we living in the Joseon era?
Are they trying to marry up?

832
00:52:30.569 --> 00:52:32.612
<i>That's not something for you to say.</i>

833
00:52:34.072 --> 00:52:37.868
[sighs] Ms. Do. Come on. Ms. Do!

834
00:52:38.618 --> 00:52:43.832
I'm simply looking for someone
who matches my current status. That's all.

835
00:52:43.915 --> 00:52:45.792
He doesn't need to be super impressive.

836
00:52:45.876 --> 00:52:47.878
Just someone of my capability.

837
00:52:47.961 --> 00:52:51.381
my means. and my beauty.

838
00:52:51.464 --> 00:52:53.091
Is that too much to ask?

839
00:52:53.175 --> 00:52:55.719
It's not like I'm looking
to marry into the royalâ€¦

840
00:52:56.428 --> 00:52:57.429
family.

841
00:52:58.638 --> 00:53:00.640
[â™ª upbeat music playing]

842
00:53:04.686 --> 00:53:06.062
Huhâ€¦

843
00:53:10.442 --> 00:53:13.069
[â™ª soft music playing]

844
00:53:19.201 --> 00:53:21.953
[door opens. closes]

845
00:53:26.917 --> 00:53:28.668
Didn't I warn you?

846
00:53:28.752 --> 00:53:29.794
Just look at this.

847
00:53:31.463 --> 00:53:33.131
I-AN.
THE 21ST-CENTURY PRINCE SUYANG

848
00:53:35.133 --> 00:53:37.344
[stammers. huffs]

849
00:53:37.427 --> 00:53:39.888
This is no time for doodling orchids.

850
00:53:39.971 --> 00:53:42.974
I told you wearing the <i>cheollik</i>
was a bad idea.

851
00:53:43.058 --> 00:53:45.727
Didn't I beg you to wear
proper court attire?

852
00:53:45.810 --> 00:53:47.854
The Royal Secretariat
and Public Affairs Office

853
00:53:47.938 --> 00:53:49.648
are outraged right now.

854
00:53:51.274 --> 00:53:54.152
-And the public?
-They're in an uproar.

855
00:53:54.653 --> 00:53:57.489
Is there any mention of the fire?

856
00:53:59.115 --> 00:54:00.116
Pardon?

857
00:54:02.077 --> 00:54:03.119
It appears my nickname

858
00:54:04.496 --> 00:54:05.789
will be trending once more.

859
00:54:07.582 --> 00:54:11.461
{\an8}<i>The regent Grand Prince I-AN has recently</i>
<i>come under public scrutiny.</i>

860
00:54:11.544 --> 00:54:12.629
Good morning.

861
00:54:12.712 --> 00:54:14.047
Ms. Do. look at this.

862
00:54:14.130 --> 00:54:16.174
[reporter]
<i>The controversy stems from his appearance.</i>

863
00:54:16.258 --> 00:54:18.885
-<i>As the </i>cheollik<i> is considered informalâ€¦</i>
-Amazing. no?

864
00:54:18.969 --> 00:54:22.597
{\an8}<i>â€¦many viewed it as inappropriate</i>
<i>for a Grand Prince at a royal celebration.</i>

865
00:54:22.681 --> 00:54:24.683
He looks so sharp in that.

866
00:54:24.766 --> 00:54:27.185
[reporter] <i>Members of the royal family</i>
<i>have voiced criticism.</i>

867
00:54:27.269 --> 00:54:30.730
{\an8}<i>They argue that preserving tradition</i>
<i>and decorum is the duty of the crown.</i>

868
00:54:30.814 --> 00:54:33.858
{\an8}<i>and that the Grand Prince's</i>
<i>recent bizarre behavior is unacceptable.</i>

869
00:54:33.942 --> 00:54:35.694
"Bizarre"? That's taking it too far.

870
00:54:35.777 --> 00:54:37.445
It's not like he was carrying a sword.

871
00:54:37.529 --> 00:54:41.199
[reporter] <i>Political circles praised him</i>
<i>for putting practicality ahead of protocol</i>

872
00:54:41.283 --> 00:54:43.076
<i>and modeling a modern monarchy.</i>

873
00:54:43.159 --> 00:54:44.953
Politicians always take
Grand Prince I-AN's side.

874
00:54:45.036 --> 00:54:46.413
Why?

875
00:54:46.496 --> 00:54:50.041
Because the people are enamored
with the Grand Prince.

876
00:54:50.625 --> 00:54:52.627
-He's so cool.
-Let's get back to work.

877
00:54:53.169 --> 00:54:55.297
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

878
00:54:57.257 --> 00:54:59.301
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

879
00:55:06.349 --> 00:55:08.601
Ah. His hype is next-level.

880
00:55:08.685 --> 00:55:10.770
-[Huiju] What?
-[Ms. Do] Grand Prince I-AN.

881
00:55:10.854 --> 00:55:11.855
[Huiju] Right.

882
00:55:11.938 --> 00:55:13.982
The executive operations team
is buzzing about it.

883
00:55:15.442 --> 00:55:16.443
Really?

884
00:55:18.611 --> 00:55:19.946
What do you think of him?

885
00:55:21.281 --> 00:55:23.033
[sighs]

886
00:55:23.116 --> 00:55:26.119
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

887
00:55:26.786 --> 00:55:28.038
I thinkâ€¦

888
00:55:29.789 --> 00:55:31.124
he's quite nice.

889
00:55:31.875 --> 00:55:33.084
What?

890
00:55:35.628 --> 00:55:38.423
[chuckles]

891
00:55:55.815 --> 00:55:56.816
[grunts]

892
00:55:58.360 --> 00:55:59.903
You told me not to pick them.

893
00:56:00.987 --> 00:56:02.155
Well. I mean.

894
00:56:02.238 --> 00:56:05.241
you mentioned that arranging flowers
can quiet a restless mind.

895
00:56:13.666 --> 00:56:14.667
[sighs]

896
00:56:15.335 --> 00:56:18.213
Why on earth are you remaining silent?
You should defend yourself.

897
00:56:18.296 --> 00:56:20.799
Of course. it is true
that you violated decorum.

898
00:56:20.882 --> 00:56:22.467
Proper court attire was a must.

899
00:56:23.343 --> 00:56:24.344
But what can we do?

900
00:56:24.427 --> 00:56:26.346
You remain so enamored with the spotlight.

901
00:56:26.429 --> 00:56:28.014
But is that such a crime?

902
00:56:28.098 --> 00:56:31.393
Is it so wrong to want
some attention in the 21st century?

903
00:56:31.476 --> 00:56:33.895
Let's be real.
Court attire isn't the most flattering.

904
00:56:33.978 --> 00:56:36.064
The <i>cheollik</i> is so much cooler. isn't it?

905
00:56:36.147 --> 00:56:38.358
For one thing.
court attire has such a drab palette.

906
00:56:38.441 --> 00:56:39.609
Such a grim brown.

907
00:56:39.692 --> 00:56:41.569
Sure. it might suit someone like me

908
00:56:41.653 --> 00:56:44.364
with a warm. golden complexion.

909
00:56:44.447 --> 00:56:47.409
I can pull off colors like that just fine.

910
00:56:47.492 --> 00:56:50.620
But on someone like Your Royal Highness.
with that icy cool tone.

911
00:56:50.703 --> 00:56:51.996
it would just clash.

912
00:56:52.080 --> 00:56:53.957
Give me a break already.

913
00:56:54.040 --> 00:56:55.750
-That's enough.
-"That's enough."

914
00:56:57.919 --> 00:56:59.587
-[sighs]
-[huffs]

915
00:57:01.840 --> 00:57:04.050
-Tell them.
-Tell them what?

916
00:57:04.134 --> 00:57:05.844
You meant no dishonor to His Majesty.

917
00:57:05.927 --> 00:57:08.513
and you were only expressing
your simple. unassuming taste.

918
00:57:09.222 --> 00:57:10.765
Just issue that statement already.

919
00:57:10.849 --> 00:57:12.642
"Prince Suyang of the 21st-century"?

920
00:57:12.725 --> 00:57:14.352
How does that make any sense?

921
00:57:16.104 --> 00:57:17.105
[sighs]

922
00:57:19.899 --> 00:57:20.984
Why not?

923
00:57:22.277 --> 00:57:23.570
[Ms. Do] <i>You can't.</i>

924
00:57:24.154 --> 00:57:25.989
-Why not?
-Of course. you can't.

925
00:57:26.072 --> 00:57:27.365
Right.

926
00:57:29.492 --> 00:57:30.743
And why is that exactly?

927
00:57:31.661 --> 00:57:32.787
[sighs]

928
00:57:34.414 --> 00:57:35.415
Are you drunk?

929
00:57:35.498 --> 00:57:36.833
No.

930
00:57:36.916 --> 00:57:38.626
Then what has gotten into you?

931
00:57:38.710 --> 00:57:41.754
How can you even think
about marrying Prince I-AN?

932
00:57:42.630 --> 00:57:44.382
Ms. Do. just think about it.

933
00:57:45.008 --> 00:57:46.509
How many are as beautiful.

934
00:57:46.593 --> 00:57:48.386
as intelligent.

935
00:57:48.470 --> 00:57:50.722
and as wealthy as I am?

936
00:57:51.306 --> 00:57:54.058
Where else could you find
such a match in this world?

937
00:57:54.142 --> 00:57:56.311
[giggling]

938
00:57:56.394 --> 00:57:57.395
Okay.

939
00:57:58.188 --> 00:57:59.397
No one else knows. right?

940
00:57:59.481 --> 00:58:02.150
-You didn't tell anyone else. right?
-You're the first.

941
00:58:03.276 --> 00:58:04.277
Good thinking.

942
00:58:05.028 --> 00:58:08.156
But I did submit a request
for a royal audience.

943
00:58:08.239 --> 00:58:10.825
What? A royal audience request?

944
00:58:11.576 --> 00:58:13.620
Where? How?

945
00:58:15.246 --> 00:58:16.456
Royal audience requests?

946
00:58:16.956 --> 00:58:18.708
I guess you really are trending.

947
00:58:18.791 --> 00:58:20.543
The Prime Minister's Office reached out.

948
00:58:20.627 --> 00:58:22.587
Lord Jeongseon is begging
for a meeting too.

949
00:58:22.670 --> 00:58:23.796
Lord Jeongseon too?

950
00:58:23.880 --> 00:58:28.092
He must be itching to chime in.
You know how talkative he is. [chuckles]

951
00:58:28.176 --> 00:58:29.177
So nosy.

952
00:58:30.053 --> 00:58:31.137
Oh. right!

953
00:58:31.221 --> 00:58:34.182
Ms. Seong Huiju has also submitted
a request. How shall I proceed?

954
00:58:34.766 --> 00:58:37.352
-Seong Huiju?
-Yes. the CEO of Castle Beauty.

955
00:58:37.435 --> 00:58:39.103
The illegitimate-born of Castle Group.

956
00:58:43.358 --> 00:58:45.026
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

957
00:58:45.109 --> 00:58:47.612
Why was it rejected?
I haven't said a word yet.

958
00:58:48.446 --> 00:58:49.614
It's okay. Ms. Seong.

959
00:58:50.114 --> 00:58:52.033
An audience with Prince I-AN
is no easy feat.

960
00:58:52.116 --> 00:58:53.576
And I'm easy?

961
00:58:53.660 --> 00:58:55.703
I'm an incredibly busy person too.

962
00:58:55.787 --> 00:58:57.580
Prince I-AN is currently a regent.

963
00:58:57.664 --> 00:58:59.332
He's basically the king.

964
00:58:59.415 --> 00:59:02.460
Plus. you said you didn't even write
a reason for the request.

965
00:59:02.544 --> 00:59:04.837
What kind of king would give up his time
for someone like that?

966
00:59:04.921 --> 00:59:06.089
Then what should I do?

967
00:59:06.172 --> 00:59:09.175
Should I have written.
"I wish to marry you"?

968
00:59:09.968 --> 00:59:11.886
Stop talking about
that damn marriage. okay?

969
00:59:11.970 --> 00:59:14.264
I feel like I'm about to
get arrested any minute.

970
00:59:16.724 --> 00:59:17.809
Hold on.

971
00:59:21.646 --> 00:59:22.647
No way.

972
00:59:24.148 --> 00:59:25.441
Is he playing hard to get?

973
00:59:25.525 --> 00:59:26.776
[thunderclap]

974
00:59:29.237 --> 00:59:31.698
He totally is. [scoffs]

975
00:59:47.463 --> 00:59:49.507
Have we not heard from Grand Prince I-AN?

976
00:59:50.008 --> 00:59:52.176
No. both the Royal Secretariat

977
00:59:52.260 --> 00:59:54.762
and Lord Jeongseon
are pressing him on the matter.

978
00:59:55.555 --> 00:59:58.391
But he has even turned down
Prime Minister Min's audience request.

979
01:00:00.685 --> 01:00:03.563
Is this his way of saying
he remains completely unfazed?

980
01:00:08.610 --> 01:00:11.321
[Hyeon] You're practically climbing
into that book at this rate.

981
01:00:12.405 --> 01:00:13.448
[sighs]

982
01:00:14.449 --> 01:00:17.035
Why did you ask for this food?

983
01:00:17.118 --> 01:00:18.494
Did I do something wrong?

984
01:00:18.995 --> 01:00:20.079
You eat it.

985
01:00:21.706 --> 01:00:22.915
[chuckles]

986
01:00:23.833 --> 01:00:25.126
Seriously?

987
01:00:26.461 --> 01:00:28.588
I didn't know you cared for me so much.

988
01:00:29.547 --> 01:00:30.715
Thank you for the food.

989
01:00:32.717 --> 01:00:33.718
Mmm.

990
01:00:33.801 --> 01:00:36.679
Yes. eat that and stop talking.

991
01:00:36.763 --> 01:00:37.764
Huh?

992
01:00:37.847 --> 01:00:38.973
All your nagging

993
01:00:39.849 --> 01:00:41.559
is drowning out the sound of rain.

994
01:00:42.185 --> 01:00:43.186
Yes. sir.

995
01:00:46.022 --> 01:00:47.690
But this is importantâ€¦

996
01:00:50.860 --> 01:00:53.738
Ms. Seong has submitted
another request for a royal audience.

997
01:00:53.821 --> 01:00:55.281
How shall I respond this time?

998
01:00:55.365 --> 01:00:56.366
-Again?
-Yes.

999
01:00:56.449 --> 01:00:58.534
I rejected it due to scheduling conflicts.

1000
01:00:58.618 --> 01:01:00.578
But she submitted
another request right away.

1001
01:01:00.662 --> 01:01:02.622
With a different name. no less.

1002
01:01:03.206 --> 01:01:04.666
-What does that mean?
-[scoffs]

1003
01:01:04.749 --> 01:01:09.128
The first request clearly stated.
"Seong Huiju from Castle Beauty."

1004
01:01:09.212 --> 01:01:13.383
This time. she put. "Castle Group
Seong Hyeonguk's second daughter."

1005
01:01:14.050 --> 01:01:15.343
[sighs]

1006
01:01:15.426 --> 01:01:16.427
Reject it.

1007
01:01:16.511 --> 01:01:18.930
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

1008
01:01:20.932 --> 01:01:22.183
Again?

1009
01:01:23.142 --> 01:01:25.770
[laughs]

1010
01:01:25.853 --> 01:01:28.022
Is he trying to get me riled up?

1011
01:01:28.648 --> 01:01:29.732
Unbelievable.

1012
01:01:30.983 --> 01:01:32.443
Have some.

1013
01:01:32.527 --> 01:01:34.320
We all work to fill our bellies. don't we?

1014
01:01:34.404 --> 01:01:35.738
Go on.

1015
01:01:42.704 --> 01:01:43.705
What's this?

1016
01:01:44.747 --> 01:01:46.290
-It's delicious.
-Good. right?

1017
01:01:47.208 --> 01:01:48.876
It just opened across the street.

1018
01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:51.170
The whole team orders
from there frequently.

1019
01:01:51.671 --> 01:01:52.714
Hey.

1020
01:01:53.256 --> 01:01:57.135
Tell them to share the treats they find
instead of just gorging themselves!

1021
01:01:58.553 --> 01:02:01.305
It'd be best if we didn't
have to work so late.

1022
01:02:01.389 --> 01:02:04.058
[sighs] God. this is beyond infuriating.

1023
01:02:04.142 --> 01:02:06.018
So what if he's a grand prince?

1024
01:02:17.029 --> 01:02:20.074
[inhales deeply. sighs]

1025
01:02:20.158 --> 01:02:22.368
Maybe it's because
I didn't put down a reason?

1026
01:02:25.705 --> 01:02:28.207
[sighing]

1027
01:02:35.965 --> 01:02:37.133
ROYAL AUDIENCE REQUEST

1028
